Day one of being 100% me started the day I decided to become an artist. And for my latest piece, I teamed up with @ToyotaUSA for a Day One celebration of my Asian-American dream. I had a blast painting a Toyota Supra, alongside my good friend @Tommii Lim! Defying expectations is nothing new to me. And following my dreams of becoming an artist wasn’t an option, it was a necessity. It’s allowed me to express myself, travel the world, and let the world know who I am. And that’s exactly what this design represents. Shout out to the staff and everyone on the project, such an honor to rock with y’all. Mahalos and Aloha #ToyotaPartner #woesmartin #streetarteverywere #graffitiart 📸 @josh.e.photography

Sharing on some personal shit-
Almost thought I wouldn’t make it. A lot of wake up calls and close calls to be honest, self inflicting and losing self love. It got a little dark. 
(No worries)
I went through the toughest time of my life dealing with lost, gaining mental health issues and trying to catch up after losing my shit. It seems to be a reoccurring theme with a lot of my close friends and family these days. Just know that I’m here just like y’all been here for me. Just a text message, email or dm away. 
Being a creative is all I got, music, art food. Pushing paint, sharing music and taste has always been a great release for me, with that it comes with good people and good vibes that share the same mind set and that can be a life saver. One love y’all I’m still here. Again pounds all around to my friends family and fans. 
Bless up❤️

This ewok armor  was created in 2003, before cats knew what the term cosplay was, I had no clue lol. I actually made it to sport in unexpected places. Also representing how not to take yourself so serious. 
I couldn’t find the vid we did of me in Seattle catching tags around the city. Also rocked a music vid with crew mate Orb and the Circle of fire crew/Soulshifters.
It’s how I learned to sew, to making hats and eventually the foundation to my puppets. Always been a creative weirdo💯
This shot, I had just moved to Los Angeles in 2008 and never left. It represents my transition back to Southern Ca. It represents the beginning of a long art career. Contemplating another migration next year but things can change. I DO LOVE LOS ANGELES❤️

Yo from Kalihi to around the world multiple times in over 20 years. Let’s keep it going. Blessed. 

Huge honor for me returning to my childhood elementary. It was here where my fondest memories were made, riding my BMX over these side walks. I took an art program that took us to the academy of arts museum where we learned basic illustration and painting classes which ended with an art show, who would of known that this path would continue with me as an adult.

I was a introduced to break dancing through the movie Beat Street and graffiti through the book Spray Can art here. (Hiphop ingrained) All my influences from my childhood from Saturday morning cartoons, kung fu theater and music were all ingrained during my time here. 
Much love to Kalihi Kai elementary principal Marc, the teachers and all the students. Totally honored! 

Mad love to @worldwidewalls for the opportunity. @mrjasperwong @amyluuwong and staff y’all rocked it💯

Thank you to everyone involved always a blast coming home to paint amongst  artist I’ve met on paint travels, shows and being able to meet other amazing artist. (New homies)👊🏾

This piece is a mural version of a print I recently dropped, changed up a little. 
I also rocked a 1/1 version over a AP print for the @thinkspace_art show for the festival. 
Available through the gallery. 

Dedicated to my family, both my siblings went here also, and my inspiration in art my Grand Father who also graduated from Farrington High. 
One love y’all. 🤙🏾

Fun fact- because of beat street my brother and I did get in trouble for writing our actual names on the walls around school, using crayons, pencils and markers. Lol

I been dealing with Bells Palsy. 
I never knew what it was, I thought I had a minor  stroke, found out it’s been a common but scary thing. It’s been a little then over a week in.
It definitely sucks, cats are still asking. It was due to stress and dealing with toxic cats, all the while trying to juggle with gigs that were already in play. I just want to get that heart rate steady and just move on without all the toxicity. 

I got a new movement, surrounded by the right ones. It’s good to cut the unwanted fat off, you usually have to deal with the chaos before figuring out your next path. Im still out here taking it easy, so the anxiety and stress don’t get the best of me. Hopping around painting, doing shows is my lively hood. I gotta keep it moving. I got lots to look forward to. So I’m good y’all- fuck the opportunist, pushing culture not for the clout. Lets build with those who give the love back. 
Just came off one of the coolest gigs, rocking a private party  with my crew opening up for The Wu🙏🏾💯
I’ll be alright pounds and hugs.
 one love y’all🙏🏾✊🏾💯
